            <p>Environment - Windows 10 Google Chrome Version 104.0.5112.81</p>

<p>Steps to reproduce:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Open <a href="https://portal.bc.bulcode.com/login" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://portal.bc.bulcode.com/login</a></li>
	<li>Click Loads</li>
	<li>Click Create Load in the right upper corner of the page</li>
	<li>Click the calendar</li>
	<li>Choose the necessary date</li>
	<li>If needed, with the left and right arrows, choose the month</li>
</ol>


<p>Expected result:</p>

<p><b>After clicking the date, the calendar should close</b></p>

<p>Actual result:</p>

<p><b>After clicking the date the calendar wants us to click month and year.</b> </p>

<p>Suggestion: Make the calendar close after clicking on a date, as at <a href="https://www.zaharo.bg/" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://www.zaharo.bg/</a>  </p>
